<br />
<font class="post">
Anyway, if i had to post my three biggest complaints about shadowbane, it would be something like this -<br /><br />1. How easy it is to mess up your character.  I really hate playing a character and building it up, only to find out later that i built it a lot weaker than everyone else.  An example of this would be picking a class subclass combo that doesnt get masteries.  It would be really neat if there was a way you could spend gold to get practice points back.<br /><br />2. Wizard pets, holy crap.<br /><br />3. The total and utter reliance on groups to level.  If you dont get in a group you're going to be leveling 10 times slower than everyone else.<br /><br />Other than that, the interface is nice, and easy to use once you get the hang of it, the graphics are actually pretty good compared to the other games out there if you have a good computer, and the pvp system is pretty balanced and entertaining.<br />  
</font>
